message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The development of male reproductive organs is stimulated by testosterone produced by Leydig cells. Testis-determining factor is responsible for the development of testes, not male reproductive organs. Mullerian inhibitory factor is responsible for the regression of female reproductive organs during male development. Sertoli cells play a role in spermatogenesis but not in the development of male reproductive organs.

Mullerian inhibitory factor, also produced by Sertoli cells, is responsible for the regression of the Mullerian ducts, which would otherwise develop into female reproductive organs.
